{#
  TEMPLATE-INTERACT.j2
  ====================
  Generic interaction workspace renderer. Controlled document.

  Two rendering modes, selected by the engine via the `mode` variable:

    mode="full"  — Fully interactive documents (VR, etc.)
                   This template renders the ENTIRE workspace.

    mode="zone"  — Partially interactive documents (CR, etc.)
                   This template renders only the fragment injected
                   between @interactive markers. The surrounding
                   freeform document is the source file itself.
                   Navigation is appended to the assembled workspace
                   by the engine, not by this template.

  Context variables (provided by the engine):
    mode              : "full" | "zone"
    view              : "prompt" | "amendment" | "history" | "progress"
    doc_id            : Document identifier
    title             : Document title (may be empty)
    complete          : bool — all interaction nodes satisfied
    current           : {node_id, prompt, values, section}
    progress          : {current, total}
    amend             : {field, current_value, author, timestamp, reason, prompt, values}
    history           : [{section, entries: [{field, value, author, timestamp, commit, amendments}]}]
    progress_items    : [{field, filled, section}]
    zone_name         : Name of the zone being rendered (zone mode)
    zone_complete     : bool — this zone's graph is fully satisfied
    zone_active       : bool — this zone is the current zone
    zone_rendered     : Pre-rendered final content for a completed zone
    zone_context      : Pre-rendered context (e.g., table of items collected so far)
#}


